Experiment 21
Implementation of File Handling Using Templats 
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Aim:

To implement file handling in C++ using a function template so that the same function can write different data types (int, float, string, char) into a file.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Algorithm:

1. Start the program.
2. Include the required header <fstream> for file operations.
3. Create a function template using:
template <class T>
4. Inside the function:
Open a file using ofstream.
Write template-type data into the file.
Close the file.
5. In the main() function:
Call the template function for different data types (int, float, string).
6. Open the file again using ifstream and read the contents.
7. Display the data on the screen.
8. End the program.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Program :

#include <iostream>
#include <fstream>
using namespace std;
// Template function for writing data to file
template <class T>
void writeToFile(T data, const char *filename) {
    ofstream fout(filename);
    fout << data;
    fout.close();
}
// Template function for reading from file
template <class T>
void readFromFile(const char *filename) {
    ifstream fin(filename);
    T data;
    fin >> data;
    cout << "Data read from file: " << data << endl;
    fin.close();
}
int main() {
    // Writing and reading int
    writeToFile<int>(100, "intdata.txt");
    readFromFile<int>("intdata.txt");
    // Writing and reading float
    writeToFile<float>(45.67, "floatdata.txt");
    readFromFile<float>("floatdata.txt");
    // Writing and reading string
    writeToFile<string>("Hello Templates", "stringdata.txt");
 readFromFile<string>("stringdata.txt");
    return 0;
}
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Output:

Data read from file: 100
Data read from file: 45.67
Data read from file: Hello
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
(Note: When reading strings separated by spaces, only the first word is read.)


Result:

Thus, file handling using C++ templates is successfully implemented. The program demonstrates how a single template function can perform file operations for different data types, increasing reusability and flexibility.